OKRSystem — Technical Documentation
Date: 2026-03-13

1. Introduction

Application name
- OKRSystem (desktop Electron client + Node.js backend)

Purpose
- OKRSystem is a lightweight Objectives & Key Results (OKR) management application that provides a desktop Electron-based UI for managing employees and their hierarchical OKRs across levels (1..7) and a Node.js + Express backend with MongoDB for data storage.
- The application exists to let organizations record employee OKRs by level, track quarterly progress and performance, and operate as a packaged desktop application or run a separated backend server.

Technology overview
- Backend: Node.js (ESM) + Express + Mongoose (MongoDB).
- Frontend: React (Vite) packaged in Electron with TailwindCSS for UI styling.
- Packaging: electron-builder produces distributable artifacts (Windows NSIS/portable targets included).
- Data store: MongoDB (document database). Backend is deployed on Render (managed web service); the repository includes `render.yaml` to describe Render services.

2. System Architecture

Architecture pattern
- Layered web application / MVC-like pattern on the backend: Routes (controllers) → Controllers (route handlers) → Models (Mongoose schemas). The frontend is a component-based SPA (React) presented in an Electron shell for desktop distribution.

Modules of the application
- Backend modules
  - `src/index.js`: App entrypoint, middleware registration, route mounting, DB connection.
  - `src/routes/*`: Express route definitions grouped by resource (`employees.js`, `level1.js`..`level7.js`, `performance.js`).
  - `src/controllers/*`: Controller functions implementing route logic for each resource (`employeeController.js`, `level1Controller.js`, etc.).
  - `src/models/*`: Mongoose schemas and models (`employee.js`, `level1Okr.js`, .., `counter.js`).
  - `src/scripts/testConnection.js`: Test utility for DB connection
  - `render.yaml` (optional): Render service specification for deploying the backend on Render.

- Frontend modules
  - `src/main.jsx` / `src/App.jsx`: React app bootstrap and router.
  - `src/pages/*`: Page-level components (`EmployeeMaster.jsx`, `OKRWorkspaceLevel1.jsx`, ..., `OKRPerformance.jsx`).
  - `src/components/*`: Reusable UI components (form inputs, buttons, layout, `ToastProvider`, etc.).
  - `src/lib/api.js`: Client API helpers used to call backend endpoints.
  - `src/electron/main.cjs` and `preload.cjs`: Electron main and preload scripts that initialize the desktop app and provide any IPC/proxying into the renderer.

Interaction between layers
- Frontend calls backend REST endpoints under `/api/*` (e.g., `/api/employees`, `/api/level1`) via HTTP (during development the Vite dev server is proxied to the Electron renderer; production uses packaged `dist` files). The backend handles requests through the Express middleware chain: logging → CORS → JSON parsing → route handlers → Mongoose models → MongoDB.
- Mongoose models encapsulate schema validations and pre-save hooks (e.g., auto-increment counters using `counter.js`). Controllers orchestrate model operations and translate DB results to JSON responses. The Electron main process embeds the frontend UI and handles packaging distribution responsibilities.

