OKRSystem — Technical Documentation
Date: 2026-03-13

Executive summary
OKRSystem is a desktop-first Objectives & Key Results (OKR) management application composed of a React + Electron frontend and a Node.js + Express backend using MongoDB for persistence. The backend is deployed on Render (managed service). This document provides an in-depth architecture overview, module descriptions, complete database design (ER diagrams and attribute lists), full API documentation, build and deployment instructions, and operational recommendations for production readiness.

2. System Architecture

2.1 High-level diagram

```mermaid
flowchart LR
  subgraph Desktop
    A[Electron Renderer (React + Vite)]
    D[Electron Main Process]
    A --> D
  end
  A -->|HTTPS / HTTP| B[Render-hosted Express API]
  B --> C[(MongoDB Atlas / Managed MongoDB)]
  B --> E[Auth Gateway (optional)]
  B --> F[Monitoring / Logging]
```

2.2 Component responsibilities
- Electron Renderer: UI, routing, API calls via `src/lib/api.js`.
- Electron Main Process: application lifecycle, IPC, native integrations and packaging entrypoint.
- Express API (Render): handles REST endpoints, controllers, model operations and validation.
- MongoDB: persistence layer; logical relations modeled by application (no DB-level FKs).
- Optional services: Auth provider, monitoring, backups.

2.3 Architectural pattern
- Layered (Presentation → API/Controllers → Data/Models).
- Backend follows an MVC-like separation: routes (router) → controllers (use-case logic) → models (Mongoose schemas + hooks).

3. Technology Stack

Component	Technology / Version (observed)
